) the full residence address of the prospective transferee while the FFL waits for NICS to provide them with the initial status and the NTN. Once NICS has been provided with the full residence address, the FFL is provided with the NTN and the transaction's status.

For a subset of these under-21 transactions, there may be an additional delay notification. For the purposes of this analysis, the Department assumes 50 percent (162,500) of all under-21 transactions will have cause established and require that the FFL be notified of additional delay being applied to the transaction (which includes providing the FFL with the amended Brady transfer date? 52
). Estimating an average of 3 minutes (.05 hours) per additional delay notification, this may require an additional 8,125 work hours per year for all FFLs in total. 53
Multiplying 8,125 hours by the estimated BLS average loaded wage rate of $46.00 (rounded up), this additional delay notification will impose an estimated yearly combined cost to FFLs of approximately $374,000. The aggregate estimated impact to all FFLs in total for under-21 transactions is therefore anticipated to be $499,000 per year. 54

